26
00:01:05,279 --> 00:01:07,599
and try to engage people with the gospel

27
00:01:07,599 --> 00:01:10,239
and the personal contacts that you will have.

28
00:01:10,239 --> 00:01:12,919
We have organized visitation and outreach

29
00:01:12,919 --> 00:01:15,040
for the purpose of strategically

30
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:18,160
and systematically reaching our Jerusalem

31
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:20,680
with the gospel.

32
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:23,620
And so we are thankful for the opportunities

33
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:25,239
that God has given us.

34
00:01:25,239 --> 00:01:27,879
But we understand that we think about world missions,

35
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:31,199
that we have a responsibility to reach the entire world.

36
00:01:31,199 --> 00:01:34,339
And we do that through supporting missionaries.

37
00:01:34,339 --> 00:01:36,900
Of course, we have our missions map on the wall.

38
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:39,800
We give you regularly updates from our missionaries

39
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,160
so that you can stay informed

40
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:43,879
and understand how you can pray for them

41
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:45,400
and with them about the ministry

42
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,120
that God has called them to.

43
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:49,720
And then we have the opportunity, of course,

44
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:54,720
to give to missions so that we can invest personally

45
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:57,559
in these missionaries being able to go

46
00:01:58,239 --> 00:02:00,040
and take the gospel to the field

47
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:02,519
that God has called them to.

48
00:02:02,519 --> 00:02:04,440
This particular missions conference,

49
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:05,760
we'll have a missionary that's going

50
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:06,879
to the country of Spain.

51
