but there's a need for more than just one missionary

53
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:13,520
in that country.

54
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,320
Of course, there are many missionaries there

55
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,199
that I know of.

56
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:18,839
And so we're looking forward to having this missionary

57
00:02:18,839 --> 00:02:19,679
join us.

58
00:02:19,679 --> 00:02:20,880
And we have another missionary going to the country

59
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:21,720
of the Netherlands.

60
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:24,699
We do not actively currently have any missionaries

61
00:02:24,699 --> 00:02:26,440
that we support in the Netherlands.

62
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,800
And so we're excited about having another region,

63
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:32,479
another area where we possibly can partner together

64
00:02:32,479 --> 00:02:36,360
and have the opportunity to see what God will do there

65
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,240
in that part of the world.

66
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:40,759
Over the past couple of Sunday evenings,

67
00:02:40,759 --> 00:02:44,259
I've shared some things that God has laid on my heart.

68
00:02:44,259 --> 00:02:46,520
If you've been here the last two weeks

69
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,720
with regard to being spiritually prepared

70
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:51,919
for this special meeting, this missions conference,

71
00:02:51,919 --> 00:02:55,119
from the life of Moses in Exodus chapter number three,

72
00:02:55,119 --> 00:02:58,160
two weeks ago, we learned this valuable truth

73
00:02:58,160 --> 00:03:03,160
that God has a plan and God's plan includes his people.

74
00:03:03,279 --> 00:03:06,399
And I'm so thankful that our God loves the entire world.

75
00:03:06,399 --> 00:03:07,639
I'm thankful that he loves me.

76
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:11,080
His love is a global yet individual love.

77
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:14,520
He loves us as individuals, but he loves the entire world.

78
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,320
And we find that God has a plan.

79
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:19,960
He's given us in his word, the plan to reach the world,

80
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:22,039
but he uses his people.

81
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:23,639
When we looked at the life of Moses

82
00:03:23,679 --> 00:03:24,880
in Exodus chapter number three,

83
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:27,919
God had a plan to deliver his people from Egypt,

84
00:03:27,919 --> 00:03:31,880
but he was gonna use Moses to facilitate

85
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,199
the work that God would do.

86
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:36,199
Last week on Sunday evening from the life of Gideon,

87
00:03:36,199 --> 00:03:39,720
we learned that every one of us has a place

88
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,360
and the importance of being in our place.

89
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:45,360
Every man in his place was the title last week.

90
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:47,740
And we had the opportunity to look at that portion

91
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:51,300
of scripture and to see the obedience and the submission,

92
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:55,139
the courage and the obedience that those men displayed,

93
00:03:55,139 --> 00:03:57,679
those 300 men of Gideon's army.

94
00:03:57,679 --> 00:03:59,580
This morning as we travel to the book of Mark

95
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:02,059
in the second chapter, we really take a journey

96
00:04:02,059 --> 00:04:04,440
to Capernaum and we learn a valuable lesson

97
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:08,059
or really valuable lessons from this miraculous event

98
00:04:08,059 --> 00:04:11,220
that is recorded in Mark chapter number two.

99
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:12,660
Now, many of us are familiar with this portion

100
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:14,919
of scripture, but let me read it to you.

101
00:04:14,919 --> 00:04:16,519
We'll dig into the message this morning.

102
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:17,700
The Bible says in verse number one,

103
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:20,540
and again, he, speaking of the Lord Jesus Christ,

104
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:24,179
entered into Capernaum after some days.

105
00:04:24,179 --> 00:04:26,459
Notice verse number one continues and says,

106
00:04:26,459 --> 00:04:31,040
and it was noised that he, Christ, was in the house.

107
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:34,380
And straightway many were gathered together

108
00:04:34,380 --> 00:04:37,140
in so much that there was no room to receive them.

109
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:40,260
No, not so much as about the door.

110
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:44,980
And he, Christ, preached the word unto them.

111
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:47,140
What a message it must have been.

112
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:49,660
And to think about the Lord Jesus Christ

113
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:53,100
teaching and preaching here in Capernaum at this house.

114
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,500
And the Bible says in verse number three,

115
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:58,980
and they come unto him bringing one sick of the palsy,

116
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:01,779
which was born of four.

117
00:05:01,779 --> 00:05:05,160
And when they could not come nigh unto him for the press,

118
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:08,059
they uncovered the roof where he was.

119
00:05:08,059 --> 00:05:09,899
And when they had broken it up,

120
00:05:09,899 --> 00:05:14,019
they let down the bed wherein the sick of the palsy lay.

121
00:05:14,019 --> 00:05:15,820
When Jesus saw their faith,

122
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:17,299
he said unto the sick of the palsy,

123
00:05:17,299 --> 00:05:22,019
Son, thy sins be forgiven thee.

124
00:05:22,019 --> 00:05:23,940
But there were certain of the scribes sitting there

125
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:25,820
and reasoning in their hearts.

126
00:05:25,820 --> 00:05:27,100
And here's what they say.

127
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,940
Why doth this man thus speak blasphemies?

128
00:05:29,940 --> 00:05:34,279
Who can forgive sins but God only?

129
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:37,220
You know, they were right that only God can forgive sin.

130
00:05:37,220 --> 00:05:40,220
Every single human being has a sin problem.

131
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:41,859
It's a universal condition.

132
00:05:41,859 --> 00:05:43,459
Outside of the Lord Jesus Christ,

133
00:05:43,459 --> 00:05:46,619
every other human being was born with a sin nature.

134
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:50,380
And they say this, who can forgive sins but God only?

135
00:05:50,380 --> 00:05:52,260
What they did not understand

136
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:57,260
and the truth that they resisted, that Jesus is God.

137
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:59,980
And we find that in verse number eight,

138
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:03,059
the Bible says immediately when Jesus perceived

139
00:06:03,059 --> 00:06:05,700
in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves,

140
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:06,820
he said unto them,

141
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:09,660
why reason ye these things in your hearts?

142
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,500
Now that must have been pretty confronting

143
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:15,299
and conflicting for them to know that Jesus is there.

144
00:06:15,299 --> 00:06:17,420
They've not verbalized their thoughts

145
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:20,380
and Jesus says, why are you thinking this?

146
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:23,140
He knows our thoughts, he knows your thoughts.

147
00:06:23,140 --> 00:06:25,500
The Bible says that Jesus continues

148
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,899
and it says to him in verse number nine

149
00:06:26,899 --> 00:06:29,540
or to this group of these religious leaders,

150
00:06:29,540 --> 00:06:32,500
he says, whether is it easier to say

151
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:36,459
to the sick of the palsy, thy sins be forgiven thee

152
00:06:36,459 --> 00:06:41,459
or to say, arise and take up thy bed and walk.

153
00:06:41,779 --> 00:06:46,380
But that ye may know that the son of man

154
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:49,579
hath power on earth to forgive sins.

155
00:06:49,579 --> 00:06:51,859
So he's speaking to the religious leaders

156
00:06:51,859 --> 00:06:55,420
and then he turns at the end of verse number 10

157
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:57,100
to the one that was sick of the palsy,

158
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:58,459
the one that was born of four,

159
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:01,459
he turns to him as it says at the end of verse number 10,

160
00:07:01,459 --> 00:07:03,859
he saith to the sick of the palsy,

161
00:07:03,859 --> 00:07:08,540
I say unto thee, arise, take up thy bed

162
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:11,260
and go thy way into thine house.

163
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:14,500
And notice verse 12, it says immediately he arose,

164
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:17,220
took up the bed and went forth before them all

165
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:21,459
in so much that they were all amazed and glorified God.

166
00:07:21,459 --> 00:07:26,140
Notice what they said, we never saw it on this fashion.

167
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:29,459
It's a great passage of scripture in Mark chapter number two

168
00:07:29,459 --> 00:07:30,940
I've titled the message this morning,

169
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:34,859
bringing people to Jesus, bringing people to Jesus.

170
00:07:34,859 --> 00:07:37,559
I think that as we look at this portion of scripture,

171
00:07:37,559 --> 00:07:40,459
I note four specific things that I wanna draw

172
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,059
your attention to this morning.

173
00:07:42,059 --> 00:07:45,179
Number one, note their concern.

174
00:07:45,179 --> 00:07:47,540
Note their concern, when I speak about their concern,

175
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:49,899
I'm speaking about these four friends

176
00:07:49,899 --> 00:07:52,640
of this man that was sick of the palsy.

177
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:56,500
We find that these four men are unnamed,

178
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:59,260
we do not have in the text of scripture before us

179
00:07:59,260 --> 00:08:01,220
nor in any other gospel record,

180
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:03,380
the names of these four individuals.

181
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:05,820
But we find that these four individuals,

182
00:08:05,820 --> 00:08:08,059
though we do not know much about them,

183
00:08:08,059 --> 00:08:10,619
we know from this portion of scripture

184
00:08:10,619 --> 00:08:13,640
that they had concern for this friend

185
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:16,179
that was sick of the palsy.

186
00:08:16,179 --> 00:08:19,420
We find that this information that God reveals to us

187
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:22,380
about these four men is powerful truth.

188
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:26,140
It's important that we recognize the concern that they have,

189
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:28,420
but we find that as this friend of theirs

190
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:32,460
is in this grave condition, that they had this concern,

191
00:08:32,460 --> 00:08:36,640
they had care and compassion for this individual.

192
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,919
We find that as we look at this portion,

193
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:41,599
the Bible tells us in verse number three,

194
00:08:41,599 --> 00:08:42,799
and when they come unto him,

195
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:47,799
bringing one sick of the palsy, which was born of four.

196
00:08:48,059 --> 00:08:49,960
We understand from verse number three,

197
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:52,960
the care, the compassion, the concern

198
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:55,659
that these friends have for this man

199
00:08:55,659 --> 00:08:57,200
that's sick of the palsy.

200
00:08:57,200 --> 00:09:00,479
And we begin to understand that this man,

201
00:09:00,479 --> 00:09:05,440
he had no ability in of himself to come to Jesus.

202
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:09,039
He had no ability to come to the place,

203
00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:11,200
to the house where Jesus was,

204
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,559
where Jesus was preaching and teaching.

205
00:09:13,559 --> 00:09:18,559
He was dependent on someone else bringing him to Jesus.

206
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:22,440
And I begin to think about the concern

207
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:25,239
that these men had for their friend

208
00:09:25,239 --> 00:09:28,840
and this concern, of course, leading them to action.

209
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:31,359
And we this morning must consider

210
00:09:31,359 --> 00:09:34,280
the condition of those around us.

211
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:37,400
I'm not speaking this morning of a physical condition.

212
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,400
And even in the text of scripture,

213
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,840
we see that God deals with both the physical,

214
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:44,640
but more importantly, the spiritual.

215
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:47,200
Not everyone that we come in contact with

216
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,520
has a physical condition,

217
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:52,719
like the man described in Mark chapter number two.

218
00:09:52,719 --> 00:09:55,039
Not everyone that we come into contact with

219
00:09:55,039 --> 00:10:00,039
has some type of inability to move into one.

220
00:10:00,039 --> 00:10:03,839
walk as this man has, but we find that every human being

221
00:10:03,839 --> 00:10:08,279
that we come into contact with has a sin condition.

222
00:10:08,279 --> 00:10:11,619
And we find that Jesus, not only does he heal the man

223
00:10:11,619 --> 00:10:15,079
physically, but he deals with the sin,

224
00:10:15,079 --> 00:10:17,639
the greatest need of this individual,

225
00:10:17,639 --> 00:10:19,239
and we'll deal with that at the end of the message

226
00:10:19,239 --> 00:10:21,439
this morning, but I want you to understand

227
00:10:21,439 --> 00:10:24,159
that when we live life, when we go through life,

228
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:27,999
when we interact with people, I wonder this morning,

229
00:10:27,999 --> 00:10:30,419
how concerned are we for their souls?

230
00:10:31,519 --> 00:10:36,519
I wonder this morning how our actions reveal our concern.

231
00:10:40,999 --> 00:10:43,739
Because true concern will lead to action.

232
00:10:46,839 --> 00:10:49,619
There was a song that I believe last year

233
00:10:49,619 --> 00:10:52,879
during our missions conference, I think it was Brianna

234
00:10:52,879 --> 00:10:55,479
maybe and Holly sang the song,

235
00:10:55,479 --> 00:10:57,919
and it's entitled Someone Cared.

236
00:10:57,919 --> 00:10:59,799
And I just want to read the words to you

237
00:10:59,799 --> 00:11:03,679
as we think about this concern of these four men.

238
00:11:03,679 --> 00:11:06,519
The songwriter of this particular song says,

239
00:11:06,519 --> 00:11:10,479
I was lost without hope, a hope of being found.

240
00:11:10,479 --> 00:11:13,519
To sin I was a servant, I was bound.

241
00:11:13,519 --> 00:11:16,999
Life was going nowhere, no matter what I tried.

242
00:11:16,999 --> 00:11:20,779
I searched for peace, but nothing satisfied.

243
00:11:21,599 --> 00:11:24,359
Then someone cared.

244
00:11:24,359 --> 00:11:28,599
Someone cared enough to bring the truth to me.

245
00:11:28,599 --> 00:11:31,759
Someone cared and now my soul is free.

246
00:11:31,759 --> 00:11:35,819
I know it wasn't easy to be bold enough to share,

247
00:11:35,819 --> 00:11:38,899
but I'm so glad someone cared.

248
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:44,399
Others too are searching for salvation full and free.

249
00:11:44,399 --> 00:11:45,719
Listen, I know that there are times

250
00:11:45,719 --> 00:11:47,259
that we get lots of rejections.

251
00:11:47,259 --> 00:11:50,039
People say I'm not interested, I don't want that,

252
00:11:50,039 --> 00:11:52,039
no thank you, so on and so forth.

253
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:56,999
But there are people that are hurting.

254
00:11:56,999 --> 00:12:00,799
There are people that are in despair.

255
00:12:01,879 --> 00:12:04,319
And they need the hope of the gospel, the truth,

256
00:12:04,319 --> 00:12:06,399
and here the songwriter says others too

257
00:12:06,399 --> 00:12:08,499
are searching for salvation full and free.

258
00:12:08,499 --> 00:12:11,999
Won't somebody tell them of the Christ of Calvary?

259
00:12:11,999 --> 00:12:16,999
The debt is paid already, but the message must be shared.

260
00:12:18,039 --> 00:12:19,599
Jesus paid it all.

261
00:12:19,599 --> 00:12:21,439
He said it is finished.

